  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/software-apps/\" rel=\"tag\">软件应用</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/05/01/natural-language-windows-search/\"><img alt=\"Stop all the downloadin' (on Windows 8.1)\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/midas/7c2b5e0d2fefc6e0808ee200f927e9e3/200083089/windows-8-1-search.jpg\" style=\"width: 620px; height: 339px;\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n实话说，在电脑中搜东西是一件颇麻烦的事情，找不对关键字就会搞得人很头大。为了改善这种状况，微软在最新的 <a href=\"http://chinese.engadget.com/tag/windows8.1\">Windows 8.1</a> 更新中加入了一项新功能。再过不久，你就可以通过日常用语让电脑帮你找到特定的内容，比如说在讲出「屏幕太亮了」之后系统便会自动提供显示设定的捷径了。据悉该更新将会于本周内上线，虽然它还不能帮你找到所有想要的东西，但应该还是能节省下不少时间的吧。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/04/30/natural-language-windows-search/\">Engadget</a><br />\n引用来源：<span class=\"source\"><a href=\"http://www.bing.com/blogs/site_blogs/b/search/archive/2014/04/30/making-smart-search-smarter.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Bing Search Blog</a></span></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/05/01/natural-language-windows-search/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20878539/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/05/01/natural-language-windows-search/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
